com.ibm.opencard.access
Interface MFCAccessParser

All Known Subinterfaces:
MFCLazyAccessParser
public abstract interface MFCAccessParser

Interprets access conditions in a smartcard object's status information. The status information is returned by the smartcard as response to a SELECT command on that object.

public MFCAccessInformation parseAccessInformation(byte[] data,
                                                   int offset)
                                            throws BadHeaderException
Interpret status information, starting at the given offset. Extract and return the access information encoded there.
Parameters:
data - the status information to parse
offset - index of first byte to parse in data
Returns:
a Java representation of the access information
Throws:
BadHeaderException - if the status information cannot be parsed correctly
